CHART.CONFIDENCE_INNER: Scatter of the ML Modell from Testing (slog)
CHART.LEGEND_DESCRIPTION: The Models are vizualized as SN-curves. The Machine learning model and the analytical Murakami-Model present a 50% probability of survival (Pü). The FKM-model relates to a 97.5% probability of survival. The Parameters of the SN-curve are the slope k, the inflection Point Nk and the load level of the fatigue strength Sa.

DISPLAY.INFO_DISPLAY: Analytical models, e.g. following the FKM-guidline or the Murakami model can be chosen. Additionally a slider allows to define the scatter as a 'slog' (logarithmic deviation). A conservative value might be around 0.045.
DISPLAY.INFO_HV: The local hardness in Vickers (HV10) is our primary influence for the generation of a artificial SN-curve. The hardness could be defined directly via a slider or the hardness can be derived from histroical data from the PLS (ger. for Prozessleitsystem). In that case you need to know your material and heat treatment.
DISPLAY.INFO_LOAD: Additional information on the loading is required for a lifetime prediction. For example the R-value for a swelling or alternating loading.
DISPLAY.INFO_MATERIAL: Besides the hardness some other material parameters, e.g. roughness an residual stress have an influence on the artificial SN-curve. With the corresponding sliders you can configure your material in more detail, what should lead to a more precise prediction. Attention: Some material parameters are only connected to the data driven material model. Step by step we want to include all parameters to the data driven model.

KPI.FATIGUE_1: Fa­tigue strength in MPa (N = 4E6) at R = -1
KPI.SLOPE: Slope within the term strength range
